<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Buckler2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Buckler,</orth> vb., to shield, to defend: <cit><quote>I'll b. thee against a million,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.241" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 241</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the guilt of murder --s thee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.216" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 216</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>b. falsehood with a pedigree,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.99" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 3, 99</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>